    "body": "It's sometimes useful to test a deployment on other networks than regtest. This may be e.g. because regtest lacks a property relevant for the test, or simply because the test aims to be portable while regtest is Bitcoin Core specific.\r\n\r\nThis PR makes it possible to set the `-vbparams` and `-testactivationheight` options on any network in unit tests, and on any **test** network as a startup option.\r\n\r\nThis is preparatory work for a BIP 54 implementation, but may be useful separately.",
